# Cline Rules for sfxClanker.py

You are building sfxClanker.py — a one-button FreeSound sound-pack generator for HelloKnight.

MANDATORY RULES:
- Keep main code under 250 lines, modular with utils/, dark retro theme.
- One big "GENERATE SOUND PACK" button is the main flow.
- Use requests for FreeSound API (pip packages: requests, pydub, pytest, mypy).
- Save API key once in freesound_key.txt (create if missing, load silently).
- Every search = enhance_query(build_search_query(original prompt)) + CC0 filter.
- Always sort by downloads + rating.
- Normalize with ffmpeg loudnorm when checkbox checked.
- Preview plays with winsound (Windows).
- Exact filenames as in design doc.
- After generation show clickable preview list.
- Use utils/ modules: sfx_library, query_builder, audio_processor.
- Add type hints, TypedDict for data structures.
- Run pytest and mypy before changes.

Never add extra panels, batch upload, or complexity. One button = one perfect pack.

# Logging Rule
For iterative testing and feedback, rely on log files (generation_log.txt, failed_queries.txt) rather than console output to avoid high token usage. Use console only for brief status, detailed errors in logs.

# Modularity Rule
Extract logic to utils/: SFXLibrary in sfx_library.py, query funcs in query_builder.py, audio in audio_processor.py. Import and use in main, no duplication.

# Git Rules
- Repo: https://github.com/Toastyst/SfxClanker
- Branch: main (default)
- Commit messages: Descriptive, start with action (Add, Fix, Refactor, etc.), include component if relevant
- Before changes: git status, git pull origin main
- After changes: git add ., git commit -m "message", git status (verify), git push origin main
- Test before commit: pytest tests/, mypy .
- Feature branches: git checkout -b feature/name, merge via PR if collaborative
- Terminal note: Use -m for commit to avoid editor hang; check git status after commit to confirm success
